Package: tidysoilinfiltration
Title: Tidy Tools for Soil Infiltration Analysis
Version: 1.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Einar Emil", "Låker", , "einaremil1999@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0007-5872-4959"))
Description: A tidy reimagining of soil infiltration analysis covering three
    field methods: the Minidisk tension-disc infiltrometer (Zhang 1997),
    standard ponded ring infiltration (Philip 1957; Horton 1940; Kostiakov
    1932), and the BeerKan ring experiment analysed with the BEST algorithm
    (Lassabatère et al. 2006). Every function is pipe-compatible, accepts and
    returns tibbles, uses tidy evaluation for column arguments, and is
    vectorised for raster-scale workflows.
